Summary 
The alert was generated from failed password change attempts associated with the service accounts oracle, sn_disscan, and ivv_ansible on RHEL systems. 

Analysis Performed 

Reviewed 30-day historical activity for the impacted accounts 

Confirmed all accounts are non-interactive service accounts used for: 

Database services (oracle) 

Discovery/scanning operations (sn_disscan) 

Configuration management and automation (ivv_ansible) 

Observed activity was: 

Consistent over time 

Limited to expected hosts 

Initiated via expected binaries (passwd, chpasswd, usermod) 

Occurring at predictable intervals consistent with automation 

No evidence of: 

Lateral movement 

Privilege escalation 

Interactive login behavior 

New or anomalous hosts 

Conclusion 
The observed failures are consistent with expected service automation behavior and do not indicate malicious activity. 

Disposition 
âœ… Benign Positive â€“ No action required 

Recommendations 

Continue monitoring for behavioral drift (new hosts, increased failure volume) 

Maintain service-account classification to reduce alert noise 

 
 

