one paragraph 

Benign Positive: Investigation determined the activity was generated by known non-interactive service accounts (oracle, sn_disscan, ivv_ansible) on RHEL systems. A 30-day review showed the failed password-change attempts were consistent, low-volume, and limited to expected hosts and binaries (passwd, chpasswd, usermod), occurring at predictable intervals indicative of automation. No evidence of interactive use, lateral movement, privilege escalation, or anomalous host expansion was observed. Activity aligns with normal service account behavior; no action required. 

 
